pulfalight.title: Increase contrast of collection box in search results
Improve Collection Grouping UI in search result set

comments.body: Upon closer inspection, the current shade of gray is as dark as it can be in order to meet AAA accessibility standards for the contrast between the blue text and the gray box. Darkening the background color further would require darkening the blue of the text as well, which is a much larger change. We can revisit this ticket if the color becomes a concern in future user testing.

The problem is not necessarily that the collection background is too light (although that could be one or part of a possible solution). The problem is that users are not able to distinguish collection-level results from the top "sub" hits within the collections. See [the Highlight Reel ](https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1SlKD4_kWFiuIMT4WHiu6LzoJ0noouYYe)for more info on the issue.

pulmap.title: Allow records to have two datatypes

comments.body:
Deployment strategy:
1. add copyfields to schema from `layer_geom_type_s` to `layer_geom_type_sm` and `layer_geom_type_tmi`. Also add copyfield from `layer_geom_type_sm` to `layer_geom_type_tmi`. (https://github.com/pulibrary/pulmap/pull/1075 and https://github.com/pulibrary/pul_solr/pull/331)
2. reindex
3. deploy pulmap changes that use the new field https://github.com/pulibrary/pulmap/pull/1076
4. deploy figgy changes the publish the new field https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/pull/5047
5. reindex again
